    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="1505"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1505">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.41/137.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                            <persName type="to">Letcher</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 27, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>You will please arrange for special train offered by Villa and take charge of
                    same under instructions from Department as to time of starting and other
                    details. Will notify you at Juarez as to names of members of party. In view of
                    your residence there it might embarrass you to inspect body. Do you understand
                    that we can have two officials beside yourself or two including you? The British
                    Consul at Galveston is now in El Paso and will represent the British Government.
                    Please impress upon Villa importance of giving fullest protection to party. It
                    would be unfortunate if any discourtesy was shown to British Consul. Delivery of
                    body is earnestly desired by widow and we still hope that Villa will yield this
                    point.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
